SECTION 2. Tennessee Code Annotated, Section 39-17-1313(a)(2), is amended by
deleting the subdivision and substituting the following:
(2)
(A) The firearm or ammunition being transported or stored in the motor
vehicle is kept from ordinary observation if the person is in the motor vehicle; or
(B)
(i) The ammunition being transported or stored in the motor
vehicle is kept from ordinary observation and locked within the trunk,
glove box, or interior of the person's motor vehicle or a container securely
affixed to the motor vehicle if the person is not in the motor vehicle;
(ii) The firearm being transported or stored in the motor vehicle is
other than a handgun and is kept from ordinary observation and locked
within the trunk, glove box, or interior of the person's motor vehicle or a
container securely affixed to the motor vehicle if the person is not in the
motor vehicle; or
(iii) The firearm being transported or stored in the motor vehicle is
a handgun and is stored in accordance with ยง 39-17-1307(i) if the person
is not in the vehicle.
SECTION 3. Tennessee Code Annotated, Title 39, Chapter 17, Part 13, is amended by
adding the following as a new section:
(a) A person who owns a handgun shall report the loss or theft of the handgun to
a law enforcement agency with jurisdiction over the location where the handgun was lost
or stolen within twenty-four (24) hours of the discovery of the loss or theft.
